  "text": "Average root mean square of the high order wavefront aberration (RMSho) was 0.545 ± 0.136 μm at 6 mm (from 0.327 μm to 0.848 μm). This distribution of corneal aberration in Zernike terms can be regarded as normal [CITATION_1] . Spherical aberration was 0.376 ± 0.158 μm (from 0.025 μm to 0.744 μm), coma aberration was 0.272 ± 0.140 μm (from 0.030 μm to 0.610 μm), and trefoil aberration was 0.144 ± 0.081 μm (from 0.022 μm to 0.347 μm) all of them at 6 mm analysis diameter.",
